== Detention ==
If in the case the main character goes to detention, they can argue with the teacher, insult them or apologize for their actions. They can be suspended/expelled, given a warning or looking further into it.

If being given a warning, the scenario will show either of these strings:
* They hope you can understand how your poor choices affect you and those around you.
* They tell you that you're a real slacker.
* They tell you to move forward cautiously.
* They told you that you are skating on thin ice.

== Reporting ==
These are the reasons your character can use for reporting a classmate or a teacher/professor.

=== Classmates ===
* Insulting you
* Fighting with you
* Acting up in class
* Cheating or trying to persuade you to help them cheat
* Skipping class
* Bullying

=== Teachers ===
* Insulting you
* Embarrassing you in front of class

=== Professors ===
* Insulting you
* Trying to seduce you
* Flirting with you
* Embarrassing you in front of class

